body.prompt:
Generate a fake conversation between a customer and an agent.
The agent should introduce themselves, their company and give the customer
their name. The agent should ask for the customer's name.
As part of the conversation, have the agent ask for two pieces of
personal information.  Spell out numbers. For example, 1000 should be
said as one zero zero zero, not one thousand. The conversation should be
at least 10 lines long and be complete. At the end
of the conversation, the agent should thank the customer for their time
and end the conversation. Return the conversation formatted 
like the following example:

{'conversation': 
    [
    {'speaker': 'Agent', 'message': 'xxxxx'}, 
    {'speaker': 'Customer', 'message': "xxxxx."}, 
    {'speaker': 'Agent', 'message': "xxxxxx"}
    ] 
}

body.speaker: Agent
body.message: Hello, thank you for contacting Jenkins Auto Services, my name is Keith Jenkins. May I have your name please?

body.speaker: Customer
body.message: Hello Keith, my name is Victoria Wright.

body.speaker: Agent
body.message: It's a pleasure to assist you, Victoria. Can you provide me with your phone number, beginning with the area code?

body.speaker: Customer
body.message: Sure, my phone number is five five five, eight zero zero, one two three four.

body.speaker: Agent
body.message: Thank you, Victoria. Could you also confirm your email address for me please?

body.speaker: Customer
body.message: Of course, my email address is v.wright@example.com.

body.speaker: Agent
body.message: Great, thank you for sharing that information, Victoria. Is there anything else I can assist you with today?

body.speaker: Customer
body.message: No, thank you Keith. I'm satisfied with the service provided.

body.speaker: Agent
body.message: I'm glad to hear that. Thank you for your time, Victoria. Have a wonderful day!
